"Power up!" (Read that in the voice of the Altered Beast guy.)

Oh, by the way, the alt. skin votes included SMW Mario, a Mario skin that wasn't another character, and "Robot Terminator" (one of Bill's Probotector skins). Alright, so what will Random pick for D-2?
Hello, and welcome to the finale of The Lost Levels on SMB Crossover! It's time to take on world D!
Mario, stop acting like Luigi did in D-3!
Now, unlike 8-4, I don't go down a pipe here to proceed. Instead, I have to press forward and deal with the cheepos here! Oh, man...
Good, and I can use these bricks to battle the next one!
Well, I don't want to use (or even qualify for) the Super Guide anyway, or else the stars on my save file won't sparkle.

Yeah, I'm low on time, but the true final boss is just up ahead. (...Hibachi? ...Remedy? ...Elixirel Daath? ...No, those are other games. It's just Bowser again here.)

Huh, no piranha plant in the pipe for some reason.

Man, this just isn't Luigi's day... I wonder if Bill actually would've been better here...

...Suddenly we're outside! Watch out for the bone-throwing skeleton as soon as you emerge. I'll just AWESOME SPREAD GUN him.

Actually, that's still not very good...
The RNG picked a Lance skin here. (Hmm... Maybe I should've just picked a "Robot Terminator" myself this time. Oh, well.)
Bah. I thought I'd stomp that first one, but I somehow didn't, and that threw me off.

Alright! Those Birdos (Hammer Bros.) are why I wanted to get here while invincible, because I remembered that spot being a royal pain for me in the past if I didn't have invincibility or at least fireballs.
Yeah, I didn't even make a real effort there.
Alright, it's true final boss time!
And then, afterwards, I'll come back and redo the level with Mario.

If you didn't click on that previous annotation, I assume you wanted to listen to the entirety of this Contra III ending music, which fits the length of the credits here really well.

And, let's watch the credits roll... Or, you can quickly skip them by clicking on this annotation. Don't worry, you won't miss anything. I don't unlock any new cheats or anything for beating the game this time.
Yeah, I figured that a few of the bricks over here would contain coins, to prevent unwinnable situations. Also, I'm sure that springboard at the start was there to help weaker jumpers.
If you're wondering why the sound cut out for a split-second there, it's because I hit Enter, which mutes/unmutes the music on the character select screen for whatever reason.
D'oh, why did I hastily jump right there instead of being more patient?

Bah, hit the flagpole too late to get fireworks, but whatever. I finally got Luigi out of this heckhole! (I'm glad this didn't actually go to infinity... or until I ran out of lives. That would've sucked!)
Wah! I wasn't expecting to actually land on the upper ledge there, and that threw me off.
...Yeah, there was a slight bit of wonkiness with the video right there. HyperCam 2 must've very briefly gone on the fritz, but we're back to normal now.
Man, to make such a careless mistake that cost me two bonus areas... I'm probably gonna want to make a bonus episode just to show those areas off later.
Uh, oh. That's right. This level has a bunch of Hammer Bros. too. Without fireballs, this could be a pain.
Ah, there's the hidden 1-up I was looking for. There was an extra brick up there (presumably to help weaker jumpers) that threw me off for a second. Also, beware of poison here.
Didn't stupidly jump into a Blooper that was too high to try to stomp...
Didn't mistime that jump...
Okay, the copy/pasted stuff stops about here. Now, the upper pipe here leads to a bonus room, but Bill can't reach it from here. However, there is another way...

Okay, I think we're doing good this time. Uh, but I can't see the pipe up ahead here! Oh, but wait! That pipe doesn't have a piranha plant in Crossover, and it was probably removed due to this being a blind jump for the plumbers! Nice!
Yay, bonus room.
Demo count: 23 (2 in this level)
Okay, please jump better this time.
"Infinity, there is no end..." ...Until I stop playing like an idiot, that is. (However, in my defense, that parakoopa death earlier was blatantly unfair.)
Shut up, clock!
Well, that was fast. And that's it! Game clear!
There's a hidden power up block right here, but I don't think Bill can reach it. Doesn't matter, since I don't want that weapon anyway.
Alright, now can I maybe get past the last remaining Hammer Bros. over here?
Come on, give me a good one when I switch to "Random"... Aw, forget it. I'll just leave it set to "Map Skin" for now.
...What? Bowser can fall down here? He can't do that in the original games! I think I should mention that on the ER forums as well.
And since there are no checkpoints in these worlds, I have to start the level all over...
Let's-a-go!
Yeah, it's surprising that the very last level of the "super hard" Lost Levels forces the player to go through a bonus room that has no hazards in it.
I don't think any of these pipes can be entered, so don't worry about ducking while on them.
Demo count: 25 (4 in this level)
BARF!!!
Oh, no! I wasn't expecting that guy to appear right there.
...Or, I could get lucky multiple times! ...Huh... I could've sworn that there was a row of invisible coin blocks around here, but maybe I'm remembering wrong. I'll have to double-check that later.
What the heck just happened there?! I totally landed squarely on that guy! I think I'm going to mention this one on the ER forums.
Decided against trying the "get him to jump into my feet plan" that time and got past him unharmed...
Aside from that skeleton (Hammer Bro.), this part isn't too tough. Just be careful of the Bloopers up ahead, but they're usually not as tricky as Hammer Guys, and I can just shoot them too.
Excellent!
D'oh! Should've been more patient there...

Well, I'll just tell you what's up there. The vine leads to the same sky bonus that I've already encountered in worlds A through C, and then it drops the player off on the ledge next to that high pipe leading to the bonus room that I pointed out earlier.
Blast! I wanted to stomp two Bloopers there, not just one! Oh, geez. This could be a problem.
Yeah, I didn't unlock any new cheats for beating the game that time. But of course, I'm not actually done yet. Give me a moment here...

Now, this is interesting. You guys only voted for Bill and Mario this time, and they both got 3 votes for D-4. So, I'll be going Random for the first 3 levels, and then I'll play D-4 twice with both Bill and Mario!
I took a quick pause break there while I saved the game (and I paused the recording for the saving process). This way, I can easily reload this file and start right here when it's Mario's turn.
Whoa, crazy dodge there, but now I'm kind of in trouble!
Maybe if I lure them to the left...
Oh, hey. It's Bill. What are you doing here?
Luigi! Dude! Stop dying to these stupid bullets!
Have I qualified for the Super Guide yet?
I thought I'd land on that Blooper, but he ascended sooner than I was expecting.
And here come the flying fishbones!
There's one last power up, which is something I don't want. Also, there's a breakable brick down here, that I guess was made breakable to prevent unwinnable situations with tall characters.
Aw, not the almost unseeable interface again. Well, screw it. I'm not going to keep fiddling with that over and over anymore.
"Infinity, there is no end. Just add one more and, you extend. Infinity, there is no top. These demos never stop."
Excellent! Okay, I think that was the last of them, so just don't screw up on the final set of bullet cannons!
That was a lucky stomp!

Wait, what the heck killed me? The lower bullet to the right hadn't reached me yet, that's for sure. I had just hit the jump button, but it looked like the upper bullet was far enough to the right that I shouldn't have hit it...
OH, NO!!! I accidentally destroyed the bricks I needed to reach the vine up there! ARGH!!! How could I be so careless?!
Okay, RNG... Please don't pick Bill a third time...
And I come out some distance to the right. I now want to backtrack to collect that star that I mentioned earlier. This is very important.
I see that this floating block has been lowered one space so that Lance can jump over it.

Okay, don't choke, don't choke, don't choke...

Wow, the odds of Random selecting Bill twice in a row are just 1%! (No, I didn't do anything special to skew the RNG. And yes, I'm still gonna use Bill for D-4.)
Awesome, though not as awesome as the AWESOME SPREAD GUN. Let's hope I get it from this power up block...
Wow, awesome!
YESSSS!!!
This brick contains I believe the only power up in this level. Use it wisely.
Okay, I want to be careful here. There's a star in one of the bricks above, to the right of the pipe, but I don't want to reveal it quite yet.
Alright, now for D-4, since Bill got more votes overall, I'm going to use him first.
Alright, so far, so good. I like that there's a moving platform there to help Lance out.

...Wait, Luigi IS the Super Guide! ...Oh, geez...

This gap here is way smaller, for weaker jumpers, of course.
Okay, this time, I'm going to use this shell on the next Hammer Guy.
Just checking for the possibility that Crossover added some hidden blocks here to use as stepping stones, but I'm not finding any.
Nah, I don't want an "M". I'd kind of like some "R"s, though.
Well, I can change the Interface Skin back to "Random" now.
And that's game! Argh, I wish that went more smoothly, but whatever.
No cheepos at all this time? I'm kind of surprised. Usually at least one or two appear.

And so, The Lost Levels come to a close. I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through them! I'm probably going to make one additional episode just to show the D-2 bonus areas that I missed today, but then after that, I'm done with SMB Crossover, at least for a while.
